<!-- End DoseChart  -->
<!-- Start Body -->

It tasted bitter.  Not as bitter as some ecstasy tablets I’ve had in the past, a kind of similar taste though, less acidic though.<BR>
<BR>
First alerts were a nice body feeling, remarkably similar to MDMA.  This was turned up a notch by touch or by stretching.<BR>
<BR>
I experienced very minimal side effects.  There was some extra burping, no real stomach issues, a little bit of muscle weirdness (no eye wiggles or jaw clenching or anything).  There was also quite a powerful appetite suppression effect.<BR>
<BR>
There was a definite increased appreciation of music, some minor visuals.  I was very awake.  Strangely, my mindset seemed practically sober, I never once forgot what I was talking about it mid-sentence or anything like that, very on-the-ball.  I may have been slightly more talkative and energetic than usual, but that’s about it.  <BR>
<BR>
I enjoyed it, though it was not much of a psychedelic, mind expanding time, at 10mg anyways.  This seemed about as mind-blowing as a six of beer.  I’d call it a feel good hallucinogen (hallucinogen in the most visual/non-mental sense of the word).  There was no really auditory or other senses affected, except maybe my sense of taste, it may have been slightly heightened.<BR>
<BR>
I could have easily handled this in public, or even around my parents or friends, and they would have had no idea.<BR>
<BR>
Although it was very enjoyable, it seemed to be almost a tease at this dosage.  I would love to see what 15 or 20mg is like.  On the Shulgin Scale I’d rate this trip as a +1 for the most part, +2 around the peak time.  <BR>
<BR>
I did it at 4pm today.  I came down around 10pm.  I feel 100% sober.  I don’t feel sketchy at all.  I am however, noticeably more tired than I usually am at this time of night, my leg muscles are a little sore, but I have done a lot of walking today.  The next day I was fine.<!-- End Body -->
<br/><br style="clear:both;"/>


